::::'''Strict Garmentmaker:''' Look at Dawncloud Cliff &mdash; even here, closest to the Dawn Device, I can smell the stench of conspiracy and sophistry.
::::'''Strict Garmentmaker:''' The elders bask in the glory of the Dawn Device, yet they lack the determination of the sky father to bear the weight of the world. They only dare to stab heroes in the back with poisoned daggers...
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Got it. This one's the Sarcastic Garmentmaker.
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Even Aglaea herself wouldn't be as talkative as you.
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} The Council of Elders isn't that bad, is it?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504069006-->
::::'''Strict Garmentmaker:''' I don't mean to target anyone, but the thought of citizens being deceived by sweet words makes it hard to suppress the anger in my chest...
::::'''Strict Garmentmaker:''' I hope you don't forget your task, honored guest. We all have unfinished missions.
